I'm gonna miss you.

12:02.792 --> 12:04.625
We found you a job.

12:05.625 --> 12:06.583
There you go.

12:08.917 --> 12:10.625
What do you think?

12:11.667 --> 12:14.041
I can't do this.
Sure you can.

12:14.041 --> 12:18.291
No, no, no, no. I...
Beverly.

12:18.291 --> 12:21.291
You got the wrong file.
When have I ever
been a teacher?

12:21.291 --> 12:25.291
Look, you got
a master's degree.
That means you can teach.

12:25.291 --> 12:29.917
No, it doesn't.
No, it only means
hypothetically that I could.

12:29.917 --> 12:32.000
Come on, Bill.
Now, it's a good job.

12:32.000 --> 12:36.166
Six weeks. A decent salary.
And you get to live there.

12:36.166 --> 12:38.333
(STAMMERING) Beverly,
I... I'll get my head
blown off.

12:38.333 --> 12:41.500
Do you know how many kids
carry guns to school
these days?

12:42.041 --> 12:44.250
In this case, all of 'em.

12:44.250 --> 12:47.500
