14:39.792 --> 14:40.667
Bill Rago.

14:43.125 --> 14:44.375
Sorry to keep you
waiting like this.

14:44.375 --> 14:47.166
Well, actually,
I needed to catch up
on world events.

14:47.166 --> 14:49.083
That Gulf War thing
worked out for us, huh?

14:49.083 --> 14:51.083
Sure did.
Yeah.

14:51.083 --> 14:53.125
I'm Tom Murdoch.
Welcome to Fort McClane.

14:53.125 --> 14:55.208
Would you come
with me, please?
All right.

14:55.208 --> 14:56.333
Give us
a couple of minutes.

14:56.333 --> 14:58.125
Sir, the extra
housing units...

14:58.125 --> 15:00.125
I'm workin' on it.

15:00.125 --> 15:02.125
They keep shutting down
these forts on us,

15:02.125 --> 15:03.959
and we've picked up troops
from every goddamn one.

15:03.959 --> 15:06.166
I got 15 buses
coming in at 2100.

15:06.166 --> 15:08.208
Fifteen!
Bummer.

15:08.208 --> 15:10.792
I've got that key
somewhere.

15:10.792 --> 15:12.917
Ah, here it is.

15:12.917 --> 15:14.083
Would you come with me,
please, Bill?

15:14.083 --> 15:16.458
You mean, go?
Yeah, after you.

15:16.875 --> 15:18.375
Ever been in the army?
No.

15:18.375 --> 15:22.333
Good. I'll show you
around and explain
your job to you.

15:22.333 --> 15:24.708
The sergeant sent
us a list of names.
WOMAN: Next.

15:24.708 --> 15:26.041
No go, they said.

15:26.041 --> 15:27.166
These are the ones
who can't hack it.

15:27.166 --> 15:29.166
Hell, none of 'em
wanted get the boot.
Ow!

15:29.166 --> 15:30.542
And they all
volunteered, right?
(GROANS)

15:30.542 --> 15:33.083
Come on, Bill.
It don't hurt much.
They all go through it.

15:33.083 --> 15:35.041
Now, where was I?

15:35.041 --> 15:36.333
Oh, yeah, that's when
Colonel James stepped in.

15:36.333 --> 15:38.250
He put out a call
to find the kids

15:38.250 --> 15:39.166
that could best be served
by this kind of program.

15:39.166 --> 15:41.000
All right. Keep breathing.
(PANTING)

15:41.000 --> 15:42.708
This is sick.
Bill?

15:42.708 --> 15:44.208
You all right?

15:44.208 --> 15:46.000
What are they gonna
catch in Michigan?

15:46.000 --> 15:48.500
(PANTING)
Bill? Stay with me, okay?

15:49.375 --> 15:51.667
The point is,
their drill sergeants
out there in the field

15:51.667 --> 15:55.333
didn't have the time to
explain everything a dozen
times over to these guys.

15:55.333 --> 15:57.291
As far as I'm concerned,
they shouldn't have to.

15:57.291 --> 15:59.166
But that's strictly
between you and me, okay?

15:59.166 --> 16:01.041
Okay.
ALL: Hoo-ah,
Drill Sergeant!

16:01.041 --> 16:02.208
SERGEANT: I can't hear you!

16:02.208 --> 16:04.458
ALL: Hoo-ah,
Drill Sergeant!

16:04.458 --> 16:07.375
MURDOCH: So the squeakers
we're talkin' about
are in your file.

16:07.375 --> 16:09.375
So why don't you just
send the squeakers home?

16:09.375 --> 16:12.542
That's a darn good question.
Ask the Colonel.

16:12.542 --> 16:15.083
He keeps insisting,
if we can help 'em
do push-ups,

16:15.083 --> 16:18.041
we can give 'em a hand
in the brain department.

16:18.041 --> 16:19.959
That's where you come in,
Wild Bill.

16:19.959 --> 16:22.041
You're it for these guys.

16:22.041 --> 16:24.750
Last chance saloon.
Sergeant Save-it.

16:24.750 --> 16:26.542
Is it much further?

16:27.125 --> 16:28.583
What's this?

16:29.208 --> 16:30.458
Oh, isn't that a thing
of beauty?

16:30.458 --> 16:33.375
That's our victory tower.
Biggest one in the country.

16:33.375 --> 16:35.583
We give 'em
physical confidence.

16:35.583 --> 16:38.583
Doesn't do much good,
though, if they got
sawdust for brains.

16:38.583 --> 16:42.000
Basically what we need you
to do is to get 'em to think
a little better on their feet.

16:42.000 --> 16:43.125
That's all.

16:43.125 --> 16:44.750
(SCREAMING)
Oops.

16:45.333 --> 16:48.750
Must be one of yours, Bill.
(LAUGHING)

16:50.166 --> 16:51.583
BILL: So let me get
this straight.

16:51.583 --> 16:54.458
The Colonel selected these
eight kids for his program...
Right.

16:54.458 --> 16:57.583
...and you want me
to teach these guys
how to comprehend?

16:57.917 --> 16:59.250
Yes, sir.

16:59.250 --> 17:01.917
SERGEANT:
Hard stroke left!
RECRUITS: Kill!

17:01.917 --> 17:03.125
Thrust!
RECRUITS: Kill!

17:03.125 --> 17:04.750
Are they saying "kill"?

17:05.916 --> 17:07.165
You betcha.

17:07.165 --> 17:09.791
RECRUITS: Kill! Kill!
SERGEANT: Thrust!

17:11.040 --> 17:12.250
BILL: Victory what?

17:12.250 --> 17:14.416
"Victory Starts Here."

17:14.416 --> 17:17.416
That's Fort McClane's motto.
Novel.

17:17.416 --> 17:20.040
Here it is, Bill.
Home sweet home.

17:20.040 --> 17:21.750
(RECRUITS SINGING)

17:23.165 --> 17:25.333
They never stop singing.

17:25.333 --> 17:27.500
What about my car
and all my stuff?

17:27.500 --> 17:31.291
Don't worry
about a thing, Bill.
It's all taken care of.

17:31.291 --> 17:33.667
Would you like
to do the honors?

17:34.000 --> 17:36.291
Yeah. (SIGHS)

17:36.291 --> 17:38.291
I've died and gone to
Gomer Pyle's house.

17:38.291 --> 17:40.792
MURDOCH: He's a marine, Bill.

17:44.291 --> 17:45.792
What did I tell ya?

17:46.208 --> 17:48.500
(DOOR CLOSES)
Bill...

17:48.500 --> 17:51.041
Your bedroom with
a closet and latrine
are right over here.

17:51.041 --> 17:52.625
BILL: Mmm, elegant.

17:53.000 --> 17:54.542
Come on. Lots to see.

17:54.542 --> 17:57.000
And you were worried
about your stuff.

17:57.000 --> 18:00.458
All-purpose table.
And...

18:00.458 --> 18:03.708
You share this
lovely kitchen with
the people next door.

18:03.708 --> 18:04.417
What?

18:04.417 --> 18:06.166
It's a Scandinavian thing.

18:06.166 --> 18:08.166
Simplicity of design.
Economy.

18:08.166 --> 18:09.500
Uh, the Swedes, I think.

18:09.500 --> 18:13.166
You ever wonder
why so many of 'em
blow their brains out?

18:13.166 --> 18:15.333
(CHUCKLES)
I'm gonna use that one.

18:15.333 --> 18:17.333
Well, I'll let you get
washed up, Bill.

18:17.333 --> 18:20.000
You got 40 minutes
till your first class.

18:21.375 --> 18:24.708
Cheer up, will you?
You're serving
your country now.

18:26.125 --> 18:27.917
(DOOR CLOSES)

18:27.917 --> 18:28.875
(EXHALES)

18:29.959 --> 18:30.959
I'm honored.

18:33.041 --> 18:35.000
I won an advertising award.

18:36.041 --> 18:37.834
What am I doin' here?

18:42.166 --> 18:43.792
(SIGHS)

18:44.166 --> 18:45.708
Maybe I could hock it.

18:54.208 --> 18:56.708
(RECRUITS CHANTING)

19:04.208 --> 19:06.208
Hi. (CHUCKLES)

19:06.208 --> 19:09.834
I'm Bill Rago.
Uh, welcome to...

19:11.208 --> 19:14.208
The first class
in basic comprehension.

19:14.208 --> 19:15.375
(EXHALES)

19:15.375 --> 19:17.875
I've never taught before...

19:19.250 --> 19:21.041
And you've never
thought before. (CHUCKLES)

19:21.041 --> 19:22.834
So good luck to all of us.

19:24.041 --> 19:24.917
(SIGHS)

19:28.083 --> 19:29.041
Oh.

19:36.417 --> 19:38.917
(MUMBLES) What am I gonna do?

19:42.291 --> 19:45.083
MAN: Left! Left, right, left!
RECRUITS: Warriors!

19:46.250 --> 19:49.583
Left! Left! Left, right!
Warriors!

19:49.583 --> 19:54.250
Left! Left! Left, right!
One, two, Warriors!

19:54.250 --> 19:58.083
Left! Left!
Left, column right, march!

20:01.291 --> 20:05.291
Left! Left!
Left, right, left.

20:05.291 --> 20:09.083
Left! Left!
Left, right, left.

20:10.125 --> 20:11.834
Squad, halt!

20:12.250 --> 20:14.125
(MARCHING STOPS)

20:14.125 --> 20:15.792
Left, face!

20:17.375 --> 20:20.291
Sir! First squad reporting
for instructions, sir!

20:20.291 --> 20:21.708
Sound off!

20:21.708 --> 20:25.458
Sir, Private Myers,
1024, sir!

20:25.458 --> 20:28.250
Sir, Private Benitez,
7061, sir!

20:28.250 --> 20:29.333
Sir, Private Haywood, 389...

20:29.333 --> 20:31.458
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa...

20:31.458 --> 20:33.959
(CHUCKLES) Lighten up. Uh,

20:33.959 --> 20:37.458
you guys
don't have to do this.
This is just a class.

20:37.458 --> 20:40.000
We're not invading
Angola here. (CHUCKLES)

20:40.000 --> 20:41.000
Uh...

20:42.000 --> 20:42.959
Um...

20:43.458 --> 20:45.291
Sir, permission
to speak, sir.

20:45.291 --> 20:46.542
Yeah, sure, speak.

20:46.542 --> 20:48.959
Sir, what should
we call you, sir?

20:51.041 --> 20:52.000
Bill.

20:53.333 --> 20:54.542
(CLEARS THROAT)

20:54.542 --> 20:58.542
Uh, sir!
I think the private means
your rank, sir!

20:58.542 --> 21:00.458
Well, I don't have one.
I'm a civilian.

21:00.458 --> 21:02.000
Oh, man.
What?

21:02.000 --> 21:04.875
You got to be kidding me.
They let a civilian in here?
I don't believe this.

21:04.875 --> 21:07.500
To teach the Double-Ds?
Who do you think they
gonna get, Colin Powell?

21:07.500 --> 21:10.417
SQUAD LEADER: Squad, sit.
I ain't no Double-D, homeboy.

21:10.417 --> 21:11.875
You speak
for your damn self.

21:11.875 --> 21:13.875
So, wait, hold up.
You in here by accident?
You somebody special?

21:13.875 --> 21:17.500
I don't think so.
Sit your dumb Double-D
ass down, Haywood.

21:17.500 --> 21:19.333
Screw you, you ass-wipe.

21:19.333 --> 21:20.333
Screw you!
(ALL ARGUING)

21:20.333 --> 21:21.625
Sit down.

21:21.625 --> 21:23.708
You wanna sit me down
or you want me
to sit you down?

21:23.708 --> 21:27.583
Haywood! Haywood!
Hey, stop it! Stop it!

21:27.583 --> 21:31.333
Whoa, whoa. Guys, guys.
Haywood, sit down.

21:31.333 --> 21:33.708
Yo, yo.
Sit down. Sit down.

21:33.708 --> 21:36.375
That's Shaolin, see?
Why don't you do something?

21:36.375 --> 21:37.542
What do you want me to do?

21:37.542 --> 21:40.083
Haywood, sit down.
Whoo!

21:40.083 --> 21:42.083
Hey! Hello? Hello!

21:42.083 --> 21:43.083
(ALL ARGUING)

21:44.166 --> 21:45.208
(WHISTLING)

21:46.583 --> 21:48.542
What the hell's
goin' on here?

21:48.542 --> 21:50.667
That dumb-ass hillbilly
talkin' that bullshit.

21:50.667 --> 21:53.208
Look at your dumb ass.
Haywood, please!

21:54.583 --> 21:57.333
Look, you don't wanna be here
and I don't wanna be here.

21:57.333 --> 21:59.458
(ALL EXCLAIM)
You got that right.

21:59.458 --> 22:02.083
So let's just make
the best of this, okay?

22:03.208 --> 22:05.166
God! Squeakers.

22:06.542 --> 22:08.041
And what's a Double-D?

22:08.542 --> 22:10.417
The whole fort calls
us Double-Ds.

22:10.417 --> 22:12.417
Yeah! Dumb as Dog-shit.

22:12.417 --> 22:14.875
(BOTH BARKING)

22:16.458 --> 22:18.250
(HOWLING)

22:20.583 --> 22:23.500
All right, I'm supposed
to take attendance now.
So, uh,

22:23.500 --> 22:24.708
help me out, all right?

22:24.708 --> 22:26.208
(WHISPERS)
I'll help you out.

22:31.291 --> 22:32.458
Benitez, Donald.

22:32.458 --> 22:35.417
Yup, yup.
That's me. Present.

22:35.417 --> 22:37.458
New York City, New York.

22:37.458 --> 22:39.542
(SCOFFS) Who would
have guessed?

22:39.542 --> 22:42.250
You're killin' me, Haywood.
You're killin' me.

22:42.250 --> 22:43.417
HAYWOOD: I just might.

22:43.417 --> 22:45.375
Haywood, uh... Here we go.

22:45.375 --> 22:46.250
Tommy Lee.

22:48.834 --> 22:52.708
Present, sir.
Tommy Lee Haywood.
Willacoochee, Georgia.

22:52.708 --> 22:54.417
Is that as small
as it sounds?

22:54.417 --> 22:55.458
No, sir.

22:55.458 --> 22:58.959
Sooey! Small?
This boy grew up in a cave.

22:58.959 --> 23:01.625
His mother come
downstairs every morning,
talking about...

23:01.625 --> 23:04.000
(STOMPING) "Tommy Lee!
"It's time for breakfast.

23:04.000 --> 23:05.792
"Run on out there
and scrape us up
a squirrel.

23:05.792 --> 23:08.291
"We're gonna have us
a roadkill omelet."

23:08.291 --> 23:09.959
Ah, back at ya.

23:11.500 --> 23:13.959
BILL: Hobbs, Roosevelt.

23:15.625 --> 23:18.250
Uh, it says here
you're from Detroit?
Mmm-hmm.

23:18.250 --> 23:19.542
What part?

23:19.542 --> 23:22.291
The part you drive
through doin' 85.

23:22.542 --> 23:24.125
Been there.

23:24.333 --> 23:25.625
Mmm-hmm.

23:25.625 --> 23:27.333
Is anybody else from Detroit?

23:27.333 --> 23:28.166
Hoo-ah.
MYERS: Yeah.

23:30.458 --> 23:32.792
Miranda Myers,
it says Cleveland here.

23:32.792 --> 23:35.333
Yeah, I lived there, too.
I lived in Pittsburgh,

23:35.333 --> 23:37.500
St. Louis, Miami, LA.

23:37.500 --> 23:38.500
Hmm.
Seattle.

23:38.500 --> 23:40.166
Any particular reason?

23:40.667 --> 23:43.000
My mother liked to drive.

23:43.000 --> 23:45.166
Sounds like she liked
that back seat
kinda ride, too.

23:45.417 --> 23:46.708
Excuse me.

23:46.708 --> 23:49.417
BILL: All right, all right.
Ow! Yo!

23:49.417 --> 23:51.000
Now, you deserved that.
True.

23:51.000 --> 23:53.417
She hit harder
than you, Haywood.
HAYWOOD: Very funny.

23:53.417 --> 23:55.166
Leroy Jackson.

23:56.333 --> 23:57.667
Yes, sir.

23:57.667 --> 24:00.208
Um, but that's
Jackson Leroy, sir.

24:00.208 --> 24:01.291
Oh, sorry.

24:01.959 --> 24:04.667
It says here
you play football.

24:04.667 --> 24:07.291
Yes, sir. Well, I...
I did for a while.

24:07.291 --> 24:08.166
All-state.

24:09.208 --> 24:10.834
Yeah. Um... Yeah.

24:10.834 --> 24:15.542
This boy was all-planet.
I seen him one time pick off
a pass and go 90 yards

24:15.542 --> 24:17.000
through the other team
like, bang!

24:17.000 --> 24:19.834
Left 'em all on the field.
Dead. This boy got skill!

24:19.834 --> 24:21.708
Gimme some love, kid.
Give it to me.

24:21.708 --> 24:23.917
Two times. Go ahead,
sit on down, Heisman boy.

24:23.917 --> 24:26.041
You should have
won the Heisman.

24:26.417 --> 24:27.375
What?
Uh...

24:28.792 --> 24:32.708
Brian Davis, Jr., sir.
Grand Forks, North Dakota.

24:32.708 --> 24:34.708
Hey, Bill, ask him
about his daddy.
Yeah.

24:34.708 --> 24:35.625
BENITEZ: Go ahead, ask him.
Shut up, Benitez!

24:35.625 --> 24:36.792
BENITEZ: You shut up.

24:36.792 --> 24:39.708
"My daddy was the bravest
and neatest soldier..."

24:39.708 --> 24:42.250
Hey. Everybody, shut up.
"...in the whole wide world."

24:44.250 --> 24:45.208
God!

24:46.208 --> 24:49.375
Um, Melvin, Mel.
Charlotte, North Carolina.

24:50.375 --> 24:52.208
Melvin Melvin?

24:52.208 --> 24:53.375
(SNORING)

24:54.458 --> 24:56.375
Is he up?
MYERS: Mmm-mmm.

24:56.375 --> 24:57.583
(WHISPERS) Mel.

24:57.583 --> 24:59.542
He does this
sometimes, Bill. Mel.

24:59.542 --> 25:01.166
Hey, Bill,

25:01.166 --> 25:05.417
he was at the BRM yesterday
in the hole with his rifle,
just like this.

25:05.417 --> 25:06.583
(MIMICS SNORING)

25:06.583 --> 25:07.750
And you're...

25:07.750 --> 25:10.083
Me? (CLEARS THROAT)

25:10.583 --> 25:12.959
Montgomery, Jamaal,
from Detroit, Michigan.

25:12.959 --> 25:16.750
Uh, Jamaal, you mind
letting these people
speak for themselves?

25:16.750 --> 25:19.083
How he gonna speak?
That boy droolin'
down his chest.

25:19.083 --> 25:22.208
Well, none of the others are.
You got a wise comment
for everybody.

25:22.208 --> 25:24.917
Hey, but, Bill,
what's the matter?
I'm tryin' to help you, man.

25:24.917 --> 25:26.750
I'm your assistant.
What's what?

25:26.750 --> 25:28.417
Yeah, well, you're succeeding
in bein' an asshole.

25:29.333 --> 25:31.375
Aw, thank you!

25:31.375 --> 25:32.417
Hey, he can't do that.

25:32.417 --> 25:33.542
Hey, you can't do that.
You can't do that.

25:33.542 --> 25:35.875
You cannot do that.
It says in the rule book...

25:35.875 --> 25:37.583
Thank you.
Just shut up!

25:37.583 --> 25:39.083
No soldier shall be
singled out

25:39.083 --> 25:42.125
for excessive abusive
mistreatment of any kind!
That's regulation.

25:42.125 --> 25:44.792
Leroy, I want a new teacher.
He can't do that.
Shut up.

25:44.792 --> 25:46.500
Shut up?
Shut up.

25:46.500 --> 25:48.708
BILL: All right, all right.

25:48.708 --> 25:52.125
(SIGHS) So much
for attendance.

25:54.792 --> 25:57.250
So, Mr. Rago,
what are you gonna teach us?

25:59.000 --> 26:02.959
That's a good question.
Anybody got any ideas?

26:02.959 --> 26:05.458
How 'bout teachin'
somebody to get a job?

26:07.458 --> 26:09.125
Uh... (SIGHS)

26:10.542 --> 26:11.834
All right.

26:11.834 --> 26:14.708
Uh, we'll begin
with language skills.

26:14.708 --> 26:18.000
Everybody will
read something. What?

26:18.000 --> 26:20.792
Not for nothin'. I mean,
I don't see any books.

26:20.792 --> 26:22.458
Maybe you do,
but I don't see 'em.

26:22.458 --> 26:23.458
You know what I'm sayin'?

26:23.458 --> 26:25.166
All right.

26:25.917 --> 26:28.333
Then we'll all
write something.

26:30.000 --> 26:32.333
Uh, would you hand
these out for me?

26:32.667 --> 26:34.208
BENITEZ: Hoo-ah!

26:34.625 --> 26:35.917
Here you go. Thanks.

26:35.917 --> 26:39.750
Um, start now
and have these ready
for the next class.

26:39.750 --> 26:44.166
Uh, write about...
Why you're here.

26:44.834 --> 26:47.000
This is where
they told us to come.

26:47.000 --> 26:50.834
No. I...
I mean, the magical twist
of fate that prompted you

26:50.834 --> 26:54.500
to gravitate toward this
institute of imbeciles.

26:55.500 --> 26:56.500
What?

26:58.667 --> 27:00.875
Write why you joined
the army.

27:00.875 --> 27:03.834
Why I joined the army.
(CHUCKLES)

27:03.834 --> 27:06.333
I joined to be with you,
Billy boy.

27:08.792 --> 27:12.208
Do you want us to, like,
write that at the top, sir?

27:14.583 --> 27:16.375
"Why I joined the army"?

27:19.375 --> 27:20.500
(SIGHS)

27:22.708 --> 27:23.834
(BUGLE PLAYING)

27:23.834 --> 27:25.542
(GROANS)

27:25.542 --> 27:27.375
(TROOPS SHOUTING)

27:31.750 --> 27:33.542
(BANGS TABLE)
(GROANING)

27:36.708 --> 27:38.500
(SHOUTING CONTINUES)

27:46.041 --> 27:49.083
What the heck's
goin' on here?

27:49.083 --> 27:52.583
What the heck is goin' on
at 4:30 in the morning?

27:52.583 --> 27:54.291
(SHOUTING CONTINUES)

27:55.792 --> 27:57.583
I hate this place!

27:58.625 --> 28:01.250
A bunch of banshees! What?

28:01.792 --> 28:04.125
You have to do this here,
on my lawn?

28:04.125 --> 28:07.750
Can't you take it
six blocks down the road?

28:07.750 --> 28:09.250
What are you doin' here?

28:09.250 --> 28:12.750
Oh, that's it.
I can't stand this job.
I'm out of here.

28:12.750 --> 28:14.959
Platoon, attention!

28:14.959 --> 28:17.917
ALL: More P.T.,
Drill Sergeant! More P.T.!

28:17.917 --> 28:20.000
We like it! We love it!
We want more of it!

28:20.000 --> 28:22.917
Make it hurt, Drill Sergeant!
Make it hurt! Whoo!

28:22.917 --> 28:24.917
BILL: Find me something.
I'll do it for free.

28:24.917 --> 28:26.417
If they like it,
they can pay me.

28:26.417 --> 28:30.792
I'll work nights.
Nobody sleeps
around here, anyway.

28:30.792 --> 28:33.166
No, no, no, you're not
listening to me, Jack.

28:33.166 --> 28:36.834
You're not listening.
Screw my pride!
I'll take anything!

28:36.834 --> 28:39.500
I... I'll write papers
for your children!

28:39.500 --> 28:40.667
Do you hear this?

28:40.667 --> 28:41.625
(SHOUTING CONTINUES)

28:44.875 --> 28:46.834
It's the sound of hell.

28:46.834 --> 28:51.333
ALL: Seven! Eight! Nine!

28:52.834 --> 28:55.458
Ten! Eleven!

28:55.959 --> 28:58.291
(TROOPS SHOUTING)

28:59.792 --> 29:01.583
Go, Navy!

29:02.667 --> 29:04.291
(GRUNTS)

29:04.792 --> 29:06.583
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

29:08.959 --> 29:10.834
Eat your beans, Haywood.

29:10.834 --> 29:13.041
That's good brain food.

29:13.041 --> 29:15.375
(CHUCKLES)
Oh, why bother?

29:15.375 --> 29:17.166
No, no, no.
Pay him no mind,
Tommy Lee. Okay?

29:17.166 --> 29:20.667
Right. You took it all,
now eat it all!

29:20.667 --> 29:22.375
Eat, eat, eat, eat.

29:22.875 --> 29:24.500
You got more than me.

29:25.834 --> 29:27.667
I could kick his ass.

29:27.667 --> 29:28.875
I could kick his ass.

29:28.875 --> 29:30.625
I could definitely
kick his ass.

29:31.000 --> 29:33.500
Double-Ds. Dumb as Dog-shit.

29:33.500 --> 29:34.667
(GIRLS LAUGHING)

29:35.542 --> 29:36.834
Dumb, huh?

29:36.834 --> 29:38.458
Well, let me
tell you somethin'.

29:38.458 --> 29:41.792
I'd rather be a Double-D
than a swinger from
the ugly tree, you fat pig.

29:41.792 --> 29:43.667
GIRLS: Ooh!
(LAUGHTER)

29:45.875 --> 29:47.542
You're bad.

29:50.708 --> 29:52.500
Nice goin', Myers.

29:53.000 --> 29:55.708
"Swingin' from
the ugly tree"?
(LAUGHS)

29:55.708 --> 29:57.250
Damn.

29:57.250 --> 30:00.250
DRILL SERGEANT:
Anything left on your plate,
we'll do extra push-ups!

30:00.250 --> 30:03.542
You know, Mel, cling peaches
were my daddy's favorite.

30:04.250 --> 30:06.000
Give me a break,
will ya, Junior?

30:06.000 --> 30:07.375
My daddy this,
my daddy that.

30:07.375 --> 30:09.834
How many freakin' times
do we have to hear
about your daddy?

30:09.834 --> 30:10.708
Eat!

30:11.041 --> 30:14.375
Eat! Eat! Eat! Eat!

30:15.041 --> 30:17.542
We eat now,
we taste it later!

30:19.208 --> 30:20.875
Where did all this
freakin' food come from?

30:20.875 --> 30:22.583
(ALL LAUGHING)
Eat! Eat it!

30:23.750 --> 30:24.917
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

30:24.917 --> 30:26.708
All right.
Who wants to start?

30:30.875 --> 30:32.708
Nobody? (SNORTS)

30:33.917 --> 30:36.417
I thought this was
the volunteer army.

30:37.083 --> 30:39.083
You tryin' to diss us?
You can't do that.

30:39.083 --> 30:40.708
Leroy, tell him
he can't do that.

30:40.708 --> 30:42.083
No, shut up, asshole.

30:42.083 --> 30:43.917
Nah, man,
he's dissin' you.

30:43.917 --> 30:45.875
Why you startin' with me,
Inbred Jed?

30:45.875 --> 30:47.417
Sit over there and shut up.

30:47.417 --> 30:52.708
Montgomery, you finished?
Is that the end of
the intelligent repartee?

30:53.750 --> 30:54.708
All right.

30:55.917 --> 30:57.750
Why don't we begin
with Haywood?

30:57.750 --> 30:59.041
(CHUCKLES)

30:59.041 --> 31:01.041
How come
I got to go first?

31:01.041 --> 31:03.417
Because you're from
Wallahoochee, Georgia.

31:03.417 --> 31:06.458
MONTGOMERY:
Get up there, boy.
Willacoochee, Bill.

31:06.917 --> 31:08.583
Willacoochee.

31:10.083 --> 31:11.625
(EXHALES)

31:14.083 --> 31:17.333
"There's these woods
behind our trailer park.

31:17.333 --> 31:20.125
"This old guy lives
in the woods there,

31:20.125 --> 31:22.625
"and everybody in town
swore he was crazy.

31:23.000 --> 31:24.792
"He showed me
how to hunt..."

31:24.792 --> 31:26.166
(YAWNING)

31:26.166 --> 31:29.625
"...how to be real quiet,
how to listen.

31:30.667 --> 31:34.333
"He said he had seen
everything in the world
there was to see.

31:34.333 --> 31:37.333
"And that's why
he ain't never wanted
to leave those woods.

31:37.333 --> 31:39.667
"Well, me and my daddy got
laid off at the paper mill.

31:40.291 --> 31:42.041
"Whilst I spent
about five months

31:42.041 --> 31:44.166
"watchin' TV
with my brothers,

31:44.166 --> 31:46.667
"I kept thinkin'
of what the old man said.

31:46.667 --> 31:50.333
"Finally, I decided
that I did wanna see
more of the world,

31:50.333 --> 31:53.000
"than what was behind
that trailer park,

31:53.000 --> 31:55.458
"so I joined up."

31:57.375 --> 32:00.375
"I liked living
with my Aunt Mavis
in Chicago the best.

32:00.375 --> 32:04.000
"But last summer,
my mother Ruthie came back

32:04.000 --> 32:05.375
"and we drove to Atlanta.

32:05.375 --> 32:07.208
"She said we don't
have to stay long,

32:07.208 --> 32:10.166
"but then she met
a man and take off.

32:10.166 --> 32:12.291
"I waited around for a while
for her to come back,

32:12.291 --> 32:15.208
"but everybody keeps sayin',
'Just go on home.'

32:15.208 --> 32:16.834
"I don't know
where that is.

32:18.834 --> 32:20.250
"So I take the bus
to Cleveland

32:20.250 --> 32:23.083
"and spend two days
staring at the poster
behind the driver

32:23.083 --> 32:25.500
"that said,
'Be All You Can Be.'

32:26.041 --> 32:28.333
"So I think about that
for a week

32:28.333 --> 32:31.834
"and then I think,
'I gotta be somewhere,'

32:32.834 --> 32:33.708
"so here I am."

32:35.458 --> 32:38.792
"In my crib,
there ain't never been
a time when we eat,

32:38.792 --> 32:40.333
"or sleep, or nothin'.

32:40.333 --> 32:43.250
"You know, everybody
just runs around crazy.

32:43.250 --> 32:44.875
"Half the time,
I don't even know
who they are."

32:46.708 --> 32:47.959
(SCOFFS)

32:47.959 --> 32:50.375
"I must be the only person
in the world to join the army

32:50.375 --> 32:52.875
"so he'd know
exactly what time
he was eatin' lunch."

32:56.041 --> 32:58.542
I wanted to learn
a new trade.

32:59.917 --> 33:02.041
Sergeant Cass.
Afternoon, sir.

33:02.041 --> 33:03.542
BILL: Brian Davis, Jr.

33:04.041 --> 33:05.708
Sir, yes, sir.

33:06.875 --> 33:08.083
(CLEARS THROAT)

33:08.083 --> 33:11.708
"Why I Joined the Army,
by Private Brian Davis, Jr.

33:13.542 --> 33:17.208
"I wanted to be
in the army for
as long as I can remember.

33:17.208 --> 33:19.333
"I never really knew my dad,

33:19.333 --> 33:21.750
"'cause he died in Vietnam
when I was a baby.

33:24.083 --> 33:26.583
"His name was Brian, too.

33:27.417 --> 33:30.750
"My whole life my mama
showed me pictures of him,

33:30.750 --> 33:34.291
"and read me his letters,
and told me how
he was a hero."

33:34.291 --> 33:36.750
Bullshit, man.
He wasn't no hero.

33:36.750 --> 33:37.959
He was so!

33:37.959 --> 33:39.083
How you gonna
prove that, huh?
You got no proof.

33:39.083 --> 33:40.291
DAVIS: I don't need
any proof!
Hey, hey, hey.

33:40.291 --> 33:43.125
Get it through
your thick skull.
Your daddy was no hero.

33:43.125 --> 33:44.250
MONTGOMERY:
Read my lips, Davis.

33:44.250 --> 33:45.375
MYERS: Why don't
you all shut up!

33:45.375 --> 33:46.834
He's selling you a dream.
DAVIS: No, I'm not!

33:46.834 --> 33:47.875
Would you knock it off
and let him finish?
DAVIS: My mom told me!

33:47.875 --> 33:50.083
BILL: Can't you leave him
the hell alone?

33:50.083 --> 33:51.291
BENITEZ: Your mommy
made it up.

33:51.291 --> 33:52.875
HAYWOOD: Cut it out, Benitez!

33:53.875 --> 33:54.792
Go ahead.

33:56.250 --> 33:58.750
"She told me about
how he was a hero

33:59.166 --> 34:00.917
"who died for his country.

34:02.166 --> 34:05.667
"I think that if my daddy
was alive today,

34:07.417 --> 34:10.667
"he would want me
to be in the army, too,

34:16.250 --> 34:18.792
(CRYING) "so I could
learn to be brave."

34:19.958 --> 34:20.958
I'm sorry.

34:24.250 --> 34:26.833
That's okay. It's all right.
Take it easy.

34:30.125 --> 34:32.625
(CLEARS THROAT) So, um,

34:32.625 --> 34:35.291
"I guess the real reason
I... I joined the army

34:35.291 --> 34:38.291
"was to get
a better education

34:38.291 --> 34:40.875
"so I could get
a better job."

34:40.875 --> 34:42.625
And that's why.

34:44.958 --> 34:46.166
"When I was a kid,

34:46.166 --> 34:49.875
"I used to love summers,
'cause there was no school."

34:49.875 --> 34:51.291
(ALL LAUGH)

34:51.291 --> 34:53.667
"I had to babysit
my kid sister,
but I didn't mind too much.

34:53.667 --> 34:56.166
"I mean, we'd fight a lot,
but, you know,
mostly we just...

34:56.166 --> 34:58.542
"We just used to kid around.

34:58.542 --> 35:02.667
"She wanted to be a dancer.
She was pretty good, too.

35:03.333 --> 35:04.458
"One day,
a couple of summers ago,

35:04.458 --> 35:07.667
"I sent her up to the store
to buy some milk.

35:07.667 --> 35:10.041
"Now, the bullet
was meant for the dude
comin' out of the store,

35:10.041 --> 35:12.000
"but killed her
just the same.

35:12.333 --> 35:13.667
"She was only 13.

35:15.917 --> 35:20.500
"I still miss her a lot,
but I always miss her
more in the summer.

35:20.500 --> 35:22.458
"After that I decided
that being part of a gang

35:22.458 --> 35:24.333
"didn't seem like
such a good idea.

35:24.333 --> 35:26.000
"So I joined this gang."

35:32.166 --> 35:33.750
That good enough, Mr. Rago?

35:36.208 --> 35:37.750
Yeah.

35:38.375 --> 35:40.542
MAN: How you doin', sir?
Let's have a coin check.

35:40.542 --> 35:44.375
BILL: Can I have
a Dewar's, please,
with seven Aspirin back?

35:44.375 --> 35:47.041
Oh.
Seven Aspirin? You okay?

35:48.208 --> 35:50.375
Yeah. Oh, Jesus.

35:50.375 --> 35:52.417
I mean, some of the stories
that these kids have.

35:52.417 --> 35:54.417
I can't...
I can't believe it.

35:54.417 --> 35:57.041
(SIGHS) It's really
somethin', huh?

35:57.041 --> 35:58.875
Everybody's got a story.

35:59.417 --> 36:01.166
You wanna hear
my story, Bill?

36:01.166 --> 36:03.083
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

36:03.083 --> 36:05.041
Not now, Tom. Some other time.

36:06.375 --> 36:07.917
Well, you know what I think?

36:09.291 --> 36:10.792
What's that, Tom?

36:11.583 --> 36:14.750
I think the whole educational
system is in deep trouble.

36:16.458 --> 36:18.583
You see, after their families
let 'em down,

36:18.583 --> 36:20.417
they go to what's left
of their schools.

36:20.417 --> 36:21.417
The teachers are underpaid.

36:21.417 --> 36:24.375
They're scared,
so they stop teaching.

36:24.375 --> 36:25.750
But that doesn't stop 'em
from handing out

36:25.750 --> 36:27.917
high school diplomas
like they were toilet paper.

36:28.417 --> 36:30.083
So that means
we gotta take 'em.

36:32.333 --> 36:34.917
Country better
shape up soon, though.

36:36.417 --> 36:38.959
We're going to hell
in a handcart.

36:40.375 --> 36:42.083
But that's strictly
between you and me, right?

36:43.917 --> 36:45.083
Yeah.

36:45.083 --> 36:46.250
(KNOCKING BAR)

36:46.250 --> 36:48.083
Could I have
my Aspirin, please?

36:48.083 --> 36:48.959
Sir.

36:51.625 --> 36:54.959
DRILL SERGEANT:
Swing up and stand on...
No! Stand on the log!

36:55.333 --> 36:56.708
You ready to quit?
No!

36:56.708 --> 36:58.417
You ready to quit?
No, you aren't.
No. No, Drill Sergeant!

36:58.417 --> 36:59.625
All right. Get the hell
back up there!

36:59.625 --> 37:02.375
Come on, this is not
that complicated.

37:02.375 --> 37:04.458
Forty-one, Drill Sergeant!

37:04.458 --> 37:05.792
No, Private, it's not 41.
(LAUGHS)

37:05.792 --> 37:08.500
You're reading
the wrong numbers.
Read the red numbers.

37:08.500 --> 37:11.000
One, two, three!
(GROANS)

37:11.625 --> 37:14.291
You've got to be kiddin' me.
No, Drill Sergeant!

37:14.291 --> 37:15.500
Three weeks, motor mouth.

37:15.500 --> 37:17.834
Three weeks, you have yet
to show me a real push-up.

37:17.834 --> 37:20.583
All right, Drill Sergeant.
I expect to get this one
pretty good.

37:20.583 --> 37:22.792
They've all got to be good!
All of them!
(GROANS)

37:22.792 --> 37:26.291
Two fingers. That's what
it's supposed to be,
two fingers.

37:26.291 --> 37:28.125
Understand that,
Private Myers?

37:28.125 --> 37:30.500
Yes, Drill Sergeant.

37:30.500 --> 37:32.834
DRILL SERGEANT:
Keep movin', Benitez.
All the way to the end.

37:32.834 --> 37:35.500
Don't stop there!
Don't... Come on!
Get back to the line!

37:35.500 --> 37:38.333
Go back to the start
of the line! Hurry up!

37:38.333 --> 37:40.041
You're gonna make it, Benitez.

37:45.375 --> 37:48.000
All right, time's up.

37:49.500 --> 37:52.125
Who wants to talk
about what they read?

37:53.500 --> 37:55.166
Benitez, come on up here.

37:55.166 --> 37:56.834
All right.

38:00.542 --> 38:03.291
What are you readin'?
Archie  comic.

38:03.291 --> 38:04.542
Okay.

38:04.542 --> 38:06.542
I mean,
what's up with Jughead?
Archie's got Betty.

38:06.542 --> 38:08.667
And you got Reggie
with Veronica.

38:08.667 --> 38:10.625
I mean,
what's up with Jughead?
He got nobody.

38:10.625 --> 38:12.542
That's no excuse,
'cause he's ugly.

38:12.542 --> 38:15.208
I mean, in my neighborhood,
it didn't matter
how ugly you were,

38:15.208 --> 38:16.708
you always had a girl.

38:16.708 --> 38:18.208
I don't know
what's the matter
with this guy.

38:18.208 --> 38:20.417
And another thing, you guys,
maybe you could help me
out with this.

38:20.417 --> 38:22.375
Mr. Rago, hold on a sec.

38:22.375 --> 38:24.708
(GROANS)
Uh, here it is.

38:24.708 --> 38:26.667
"Come on, Archie,
let's go to the
Malt Shop-ee."

38:26.667 --> 38:27.875
What the hell's
a Malt Shop-ee?

38:27.875 --> 38:29.625
They're always
talking about...
MONTGOMERY: Benitez.

38:29.625 --> 38:30.875
What's a Malt Shop-ee?
You guys know?

38:30.875 --> 38:34.250
Come here. Bring your
stupid ass over here.
Come here.

38:34.250 --> 38:35.417
What's the matter with you?

38:35.417 --> 38:36.708
What do you mean?

38:36.708 --> 38:39.375
What are you doin'
readin' a comic book?

38:39.375 --> 38:40.708
He said we could bring
anything we wanted.

38:40.708 --> 38:42.375
I brought a comic book.
I like comic books.

38:42.375 --> 38:44.083
All right. Knock it off.

38:44.083 --> 38:46.417
You're here for education,
not to read comic books.
You're embarrassing me, boy.

38:46.417 --> 38:47.708
Jesus!
That's stupid.

38:47.708 --> 38:49.750
You could've got
something else at the P.X.

38:49.750 --> 38:52.375
Yeah, like  Batman
or  Superman...
True that, man.

38:52.375 --> 38:53.875
Come on, shut up!
...or  Spider-Man.

38:54.583 --> 38:56.458
(SIGHS) Oh, God.
BENITEZ: They scare me.

38:56.458 --> 38:59.583
(MONTGOMERY LAUGHS)
Bunch of hyenas.

38:59.583 --> 39:01.250
What's the book
you got, Mr. Rago?

39:02.291 --> 39:04.041
This?
Yeah.

39:04.417 --> 39:05.750
This is called  Hamlet.

39:05.750 --> 39:08.625
Hamlet.  Yo, that's about
a little-bitty pig, right?

39:08.625 --> 39:11.458
No, it ain't about
a little-bitty pig.

39:11.458 --> 39:13.083
What's it about,
Billy boy?

39:14.291 --> 39:16.417
It's about

39:16.417 --> 39:21.125
sex, murder,
incest, insanity.

39:21.125 --> 39:22.417
Ooh!

39:22.417 --> 39:24.500
Shoot. Beats the hell
out of this garbage
I'm readin'.

39:24.500 --> 39:26.083
(CLICKS TONGUE) Guns.

39:26.083 --> 39:27.375
Sure does.

39:27.375 --> 39:30.417
Pretty much beats the heck
out of any book ever written.

39:30.417 --> 39:31.417
All right, Leroy.
LEROY: Yeah?

39:31.417 --> 39:32.583
What are you readin'?

39:32.583 --> 39:35.834
Uh,  Sports Illustrated.
"Faces in the Crowd"
section.

39:35.834 --> 39:38.291
You know,
why don't you tell us
more about your book?

39:38.291 --> 39:39.500
Sounds more interesting.

39:39.500 --> 39:41.625
BENITEZ: Yeah, who wrote it?

39:41.625 --> 39:43.792
Well, it was written
by William Shakespeare.

39:43.792 --> 39:45.834
You guys ever hear
of Shakespeare?

39:45.834 --> 39:48.625
Yeah, I heard of him.
That guy's in Central Park
every summer.

39:48.625 --> 39:50.667
Damn. The dude must've
got mugged a lot.

39:50.667 --> 39:53.625
He's been dead
for almost 400 years.

39:53.625 --> 39:54.792
You see that?
They killed him.
Yeah.

39:54.792 --> 39:57.458
They killed him.
New Yorkers.
Yeah.

39:57.458 --> 39:59.166
He wrote plays.

40:01.417 --> 40:02.792
Plays.

40:02.792 --> 40:05.291
You know,
like TV without the box.

40:06.333 --> 40:08.458
Mmm.
Ah.

40:08.458 --> 40:12.166
They didn't have
any TVs back then,
or movies.

40:12.625 --> 40:14.792
Or that many books, even.

40:14.792 --> 40:17.750
So everybody went
to the theater. Everybody.

40:17.750 --> 40:21.166
Kings, queens, right down
to the working stiffs.

40:21.875 --> 40:23.542
Hey, so, why don't you
read us some of that?

40:23.542 --> 40:25.500
Skip to the page
with some incest

40:25.500 --> 40:27.166
so we can make Haywood
feel at home.

40:27.667 --> 40:30.166
MONTGOMERY: Sooey!
(LAUGHTER)

40:30.166 --> 40:33.041
No, you... You guys
don't want to hear
about  Hamlet.

40:33.041 --> 40:36.667
What? What? What?
I guess we're not
smart enough, huh?

40:36.667 --> 40:38.708
No, no, no, no, no.
It's just very...

40:38.708 --> 40:40.375
I don't know, it's...
MONTGOMERY: Here we go.

40:40.375 --> 40:42.291
What, what? It's just what?

40:42.291 --> 40:43.542
It's complicated.

40:43.542 --> 40:46.333
So? We're here.
We're listenin'.

40:48.500 --> 40:50.166
(CLEARS THROAT)

40:54.417 --> 40:56.041
Sit down.

41:00.500 --> 41:02.208
Okay, okay.

41:02.917 --> 41:05.375
All right,
here's the deal. Um...

41:08.542 --> 41:10.208
Hamlet is, uh...

41:13.250 --> 41:15.041
Uh, he's a prince.

41:15.375 --> 41:17.750
All right? And, uh...

41:17.750 --> 41:20.875
And he's away at college.
MONTGOMERY: Ah, rich kid.

41:20.875 --> 41:23.917
Right? And he...
He gets word that
his father died.

41:23.917 --> 41:26.875
Oh, no, Davis, please,
don't start cryin',
please.

41:26.875 --> 41:29.250
Leave me alone, Benitez!
(CHUCKLING)

41:29.250 --> 41:30.000
Forget about it.

41:30.000 --> 41:32.250
